{"id":7900,"date":"2019-06-21T17:01:01","date_gmt":"2019-06-21T17:01:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.fluentco.com\/?p=7900"},"modified":"2020-12-29T02:19:13","modified_gmt":"2020-12-29T02:19:13","slug":"fluent-service-day-2019","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.fluentco.com\/blog\/fluent-service-day-2019\/","title":{"rendered":"Reflections on Fluent Service Day"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>This spring, we held our largest annual Service Day to date, sending out 130 employees to 15 volunteer sites across 7 states.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fluent employees engaged in a variety of service initiatives including soup kitchens, food drives, pet shelters, early education and elementary schools, after-school sports and arts programs, a beach cleanup, and an urban garden in Brooklyn. As a team, we dedicated nearly 400 person-hours to helping the community.&nbsp; Across locations, we served over 1000 meals, cared for more than 100 animals, and spent time in classrooms mentoring dozens of students.&nbsp;   <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fluent&#8217;s remote employees also participated in Service Day activities, dedicating half a day to give back to community initiatives in their local areas.&nbsp; These included tornado disaster relief in Ohio, flood relief in Little Rock, Arkansas, a sports program in upstate NY, and a food bank in Washington DC.&nbsp; Fluent\u2019s Florida office also participated in a beach clean-up at nearby Deerfield Beach.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We appreciate the hard work and dedication of all those who helped to make Fluent Service Day 2019 a huge success. Whether we are collaborating in the workplace or volunteering at a soup kitchen, our core values at Fluent drive us to learn, connect, innovate, and succeed in our local communities and beyond. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"metaslider-id-7901\" style=\"max-width: 700px;\" class=\"ml-slider-3-20-3 metaslider metaslider-flex metaslider-7901 ml-slider  alignnormal\">\n    <div id=\"metaslider_container_7901\">\n  